Heat oven to 300 degrees F. Combine cookie crumbs and butter; press firmly on bottom and halfway up side of 9-inch springform pan. In large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth. Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Pour into prepared pan. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until edge springs back when lightly touched (center will be slightly soft). Cool. Chill. Garnish as desired. Store leftovers covered in refrigerator.